{
  "stem": "8892.5",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So there we opened up in a brand new shopping center from scratch, a store, and we both worked in it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "48 years.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was last week.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Long time.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Thank God.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I have to tell you, Fran.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First I was very hesitant, very reluctant if I'm going to give this interview.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't know if I can go through with it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then when I thought about it, I said, the memory of my sister [CRYING] who suffered and didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My father evidently suffered and didn't make it and, and all the relatives, and all the six million Jews deserved it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I want my grandchildren to know that when they hear this, it's not a story like when we read the, the Pesach, when we read the stories.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all just reading it as a story and can't even visualize that it was really that torture and that all this horrible things were happening.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I feel if they're going to see me, especially my grandchildren, they can tell their own children that  this was actually happening, and that was my grandmother who's telling the story.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I hope to God that never, never do we forget this, and never, in any of their lifetime, ever, will be another Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if they ever, life will change for them, I just hope that they'll be strong enough, they'll have faith, they'll have belief in themself that they have to fight life.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because life is very unpredictable, and you don't know what's going to happen from next day to another day.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I really, truly hope that this story can help them face up.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we Jewish people suffered so much.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
